<div class="pipeline-diagram font-mono text-xs text-text-dim leading-relaxed overflow-x-auto">
  <pre class="bg-surface border border-border rounded-xl p-5 text-[0.72rem] leading-5 font-mono">
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                      Argus CRAG Pipeline                            │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

  Input (query / draft / prompt)
          │
          ▼
  ┌──────────────────┐
  │  Flash-Lite       │  PROCESS: replace named entities with stable placeholders
  │  Anonymizer       │           (PARTY_A, ORG_001, ...). Per-session two-way map
  │                   │           lives in server process memory only. Never written
  │                   │           to disk or any third-party store.
  └──────────┬───────┘
             │ anonymized text
             ▼
  ┌──────────────────┐
  │  Cohere Embed v4 │  PROCESS: 1024-dim embedding of the anonymized query.
  │  (1024-dim)      │           Same model used at corpus ingest time so the
  │                   │           vector space matches the index.
  └──────────┬───────┘
             │ query vector
             ▼
  ┌══════════════════┐
  ║  Neon pgvector   ║  DATA LAYER: 11,266 corpus chunks (22 playbook +
  ║  (IVFFlat)       ║              7,067 CUAD + 4,177 MAUD).
  ║                   ║  PROCESS:    cosine-similarity → top-12 candidates.
  └══════════┬═══════┘
             │ top-12 + optional session context (see ↓)
             │
             │      ┌══════════════════┐
             │      ║  Supermemory     ║  DATA LAYER: per-session uploaded
             │ ←─── ║  kind=context    ║  documents (NotebookLM-style "Add
             │      ║  (read)          ║  source"). Skipped when session has
             │      └══════════════════┘  no uploads.
             ▼
  ┌──────────────────┐
  │  Cohere Rerank   │  PROCESS: cross-encoder re-scores candidates by
  │  3.5  [Hub only] │           semantic relevance. Catches paraphrases
  │                   │           that cosine distance misses.
  └──────────┬───────┘
             │ reranked context
             ▼
  ┌──────────────────┐
  │  Gemini 2.5      │  PROCESS: generate.
  │  Flash           │           Hub  → structured JSON, ≤14 issues + drafts
  │                   │           Chat → streamed prose + [n] citations
  └──────────┬───────┘
             │
   ┌─────────┴─────────────────────────────────┐
   │                                           │
   ▼  Drafting & Review Hub                    ▼  Ask the Corpus
  ┌──────────────────┐                        ┌──────────────────┐
  │  Editing Hub     │   PROCESS: per-change  │  Stream answer   │   PROCESS: token-by-
  │  workspace       │   accept / reject /    │  to browser via  │   token SSE; rehydrate
  │                   │   inline rewrite      │  Server-Sent     │   placeholders →
  │                   │                        │  Events          │   original names
  └──────────┬───────┘                        └──────────┬───────┘
             │ baked artifacts                            │
             ▼                                            ▼
  redline.docx · clean.docx ·                   ┌══════════════════┐
  memo.docx · register.json                     ║ Supermemory      ║  DATA LAYER:
             │                                  ║ kind=            ║  anonymized
             ▼                                  ║ chat_exchange    ║  Q&A pair,
  ┌══════════════════┐                          ║ (write)          ║  TTL 24h.
  ║  Supermemory     ║  DATA LAYER: anonymized  └══════════════════┘
  ║ kind=review_     ║  bake summary with
  ║  summary (write) ║  ≤14 change records.
  └══════════════════┘  TTL 24h.

  ↪ PII firewall regex re-screens every Supermemory write (second layer of defense)
  ↪ Anonymizer rehydrates entity names on the way back to the user before display
  ↪ Per-session 24h TTL on all Supermemory data (server-side, account-level setting)
  ↪ All in-process state (anonymizer map, gunicorn cache) discarded on worker recycle
</pre>
</div>
